prompt: Show codes and fates of missions, and names of ships involved.
completion: SELECT T1.Code ,  T1.Fate ,  T2.Name FROM mission AS T1 JOIN ship AS T2 ON T1.Ship_ID  =  T2.Ship_ID

prompt: What are the name, population, and life expectancy of the largest Asian country by land?
completion: SELECT Name ,  Population ,  LifeExpectancy FROM country WHERE Continent  =  "Asia" ORDER BY SurfaceArea DESC LIMIT 1

prompt: How many departments are in the division AS?
completion: SELECT count(*) FROM DEPARTMENT WHERE Division  =  "AS"

prompt: which course has most number of registered students?
completion: SELECT T1.course_name FROM courses AS T1 JOIN student_course_registrations AS T2 ON T1.course_id = T2.course_Id GROUP BY T1.course_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

prompt: What are the names of all products?
completion: SELECT Name FROM Products

prompt: Show the reign and days held of wrestlers.
completion: SELECT Reign ,  Days_held FROM wrestler

prompt: Find the first and last name of all the students of age 18 who have vice president votes.
completion: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Fname ,  T1.LName FROM STUDENT AS T1 JOIN VOTING_RECORD AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  T2.VICE_President_VOTE WHERE T1.age  =  18

prompt: How many different types of rooms are there?
completion: SELECT count(DISTINCT roomtype) FROM room

prompt: which countries have more than 2 airports?
completion: SELECT country FROM airport GROUP BY country HAVING count(*)  >  2

prompt: How many students are there?
completion: SELECT count(*) FROM student

prompt: What is the average gpa of the students enrolled in the course with code ACCT-211?
completion: SELECT avg(T2.stu_gpa) FROM enroll AS T1 JOIN student AS T2 ON T1.stu_num  =  T2.stu_num JOIN CLASS AS T3 ON T1.class_code  =  T3.class_code WHERE T3.crs_code  =  'ACCT-211'

prompt: What are the name and the nationality of the host of the highest age?
completion: SELECT Name ,  Nationality FROM HOST ORDER BY Age DESC LIMIT 1

prompt: Give me the zip code where the average mean humidity is below 70 and at least 100 trips took place.
completion: SELECT zip_code FROM weather GROUP BY zip_code HAVING avg(mean_humidity)  <  70 INTERSECT SELECT zip_code FROM trip GROUP BY zip_code HAVING count(*)  >=  100

prompt: List all public schools and their locations.
completion: SELECT school ,  LOCATION FROM university WHERE affiliation  =  'Public'

prompt: How many dogs went through any treatments?
completion: SELECT count(DISTINCT dog_id) FROM Treatments

prompt: What are the locations that have gas stations owned by a company with a market value greater than 100?
completion: SELECT T3.location FROM station_company AS T1 JOIN company AS T2 ON T1.company_id  =  T2.company_id JOIN gas_station AS T3 ON T1.station_id  =  T3.station_id WHERE T2.market_value  >  100

prompt: What are the last names of students studying major 50?
completion: SELECT LName FROM STUDENT WHERE Major  =  50

prompt: Find the name of airline which runs the most number of routes.
completion: SELECT T1.name FROM airlines AS T1 JOIN routes AS T2 ON T1.alid  =  T2.alid GROUP BY T1.name ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

prompt: Count the number of patients who stayed in room 112.
completion: SELECT count(patient) FROM stay WHERE room  =  112

prompt: List all the information about course authors and tutors in alphabetical order of the personal name.
completion: SELECT * FROM Course_Authors_and_Tutors ORDER BY personal_name

prompt: List the names, phone numbers, and emails of all customers sorted by their dates of becoming customers.
completion: SELECT customer_name ,  customer_phone ,  customer_email FROM Customers ORDER BY date_became_customer

prompt: Give me the product type, name and price for all the products supplied by supplier id 3.
completion: SELECT T2.product_type_code ,  T2.product_name ,  T2.product_price FROM product_suppliers AS T1 JOIN products AS T2 ON T1.product_id  =  T2.product_id WHERE T1.supplier_id  =  3

prompt: Find the name, account type, and account balance of the customer who has the highest credit score.
completion: SELECT cust_name ,  acc_type ,  acc_bal FROM customer ORDER BY credit_score DESC LIMIT 1

prompt: What are the years, titles, and publishers for all books, ordered by year descending?
completion: SELECT YEAR ,  book_title ,  publisher FROM book_club ORDER BY YEAR DESC

prompt: What are the different main industries for all companies?
completion: SELECT DISTINCT main_industry FROM company

prompt: How many different results are there for the battles?
completion: SELECT count(DISTINCT RESULT) FROM battle

prompt: How many rooms are there?
completion: SELECT count(*) FROM Rooms;

prompt: What is the highest elevation of an airport in the country of Iceland?
completion: SELECT max(elevation) FROM airports WHERE country  =  'Iceland'

prompt: Find the department name and room of the course INTRODUCTION TO COMPUTER SCIENCE.
completion: SELECT T2.Dname ,  T2.Room FROM COURSE AS T1 JOIN DEPARTMENT AS T2 ON T1.DNO  =  T2.DNO WHERE T1.CName  =  "INTRODUCTION TO COMPUTER SCIENCE"

prompt: What are the first and last names of all the female students who have president votes?
completion: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Fname ,  T1.LName FROM STUDENT AS T1 JOIN VOTING_RECORD AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  T2.President_VOTE WHERE T1.sex  =  "F"

prompt: Show the names of customers who have at least 2 mailshots with outcome code 'Order'.
completion: SELECT T2.customer_name FROM mailshot_customers AS T1 JOIN customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id WHERE outcome_code  =  'Order' GROUP BY T1.customer_id HAVING count(*)  >=  2

prompt: what are the order id and customer id of the oldest order?
completion: SELECT order_id ,  customer_id FROM orders ORDER BY date_order_placed LIMIT 1

prompt: What are the names of all races held after 2000 in Spain?
completion: SELECT DISTINCT T1.name FROM races AS T1 JOIN circuits AS T2 ON T1.circuitid = T2.circuitid WHERE T2.country = "Spain" AND T1.year > 2000

prompt: What are the different ids and names of the stations that have had more than 12 bikes available?
completion: SELECT DISTINCT T1.id ,  T1.name FROM station AS T1 JOIN status AS T2 ON T1.id  =  T2.station_id WHERE T2.bikes_available  >  12

prompt: List the name of products in ascending order of price.
completion: SELECT Product_Name FROM Products ORDER BY Product_Price ASC

prompt: Which claims caused more than 2 settlements or have the maximum claim value? List the date the claim was made and the claim id.
completion: SELECT T1.Date_Claim_Made ,  T1.Claim_id FROM Claims AS T1 JOIN Settlements AS T2 ON T1.Claim_id  =  T2.Claim_id GROUP BY T1.Claim_id HAVING count(*)  >  2 UNION SELECT T1.Date_Claim_Made ,  T1.Claim_id FROM Claims AS T1 JOIN Settlements AS T2 ON T1.Claim_id  =  T2.Claim_id WHERE T1.Amount_Claimed  =  ( SELECT max(Amount_Claimed) FROM Claims )

prompt: What are the ids of all employees that don't have certificates?
completion: SELECT eid FROM Employee EXCEPT SELECT eid FROM Certificate

prompt: Show the players and the years played.
completion: SELECT Player ,  Years_Played FROM player

prompt: Find the login name of the course author that teaches the course with name "advanced database".
completion: SELECT T1.login_name FROM Course_Authors_and_Tutors AS T1 JOIN Courses AS T2 ON T1.author_id  =  T2.author_id WHERE T2.course_name  =  "advanced database"

prompt: Find the names of the visitors whose membership level is higher than 4, and order the results by the level from high to low.
completion: SELECT name FROM visitor WHERE Level_of_membership  >  4 ORDER BY Level_of_membership DESC

prompt: What are the details of the project with no outcomes?
completion: SELECT project_details FROM Projects WHERE project_id NOT IN ( SELECT project_id FROM Project_outcomes )

prompt: Return the weight of the shortest person.
completion: SELECT Weight FROM people ORDER BY Height ASC LIMIT 1

prompt: What is the highest salary among each team? List the team name, id and maximum salary.
completion: SELECT T1.name ,  T1.team_id ,  max(T2.salary) FROM team AS T1 JOIN salary AS T2 ON T1.team_id  =  T2.team_id GROUP BY T1.team_id;

prompt: Find the count and code of the job has most employees.
completion: SELECT emp_jobcode ,  count(*) FROM employee GROUP BY emp_jobcode ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

prompt: How many counties are there in total?
completion: SELECT count(*) FROM county

prompt: What are the gender and occupation of players?
completion: SELECT Gender ,  Occupation FROM player

prompt: Show the most common nationality for journalists.
completion: SELECT Nationality FROM journalist GROUP BY Nationality ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC LIMIT 1

prompt: How many flights do we have?
completion: SELECT count(*) FROM Flight

prompt: Return the apartment number and the number of rooms for each apartment.
completion: SELECT apt_number ,  room_count FROM Apartments

prompt: Find the name of instructor who is the advisor of the student who has the highest number of total credits.
completion: SELECT T2.name FROM advisor AS T1 JOIN instructor AS T2 ON T1.i_id  =  T2.id JOIN student AS T3 ON T1.s_id  =  T3.id ORDER BY T3.tot_cred DESC LIMIT 1

prompt: What is the name of the department with the most students enrolled?
completion: SELECT T4.dept_name FROM CLASS AS T1 JOIN enroll AS T2 ON T1.class_code  =  T2.class_code JOIN course AS T3 ON T1.crs_code  =  T3.crs_code JOIN department AS T4 ON T3.dept_code  =  T4.dept_code GROUP BY T3.dept_code ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

prompt: Show the customer ids and firstname without a credit card.
completion: SELECT customer_id ,  customer_first_name FROM Customers EXCEPT SELECT T1.customer_id ,  T2.customer_first_name FROM Customers_cards AS T1 JOIN Customers AS T2 ON T1.customer_id  =  T2.customer_id WHERE card_type_code  =  "Credit"

prompt: Find the name of the patient who made the appointment with the most recent start date.
completion: SELECT T1.name FROM patient AS T1 JOIN appointment AS T2 ON T1.ssn = T2.patient ORDER BY T2.start DESC LIMIT 1

prompt: List all the scientists' names, their projects' names, and the hours worked by that scientist on each project, in alphabetical order of project name, and then scientist name.
completion: SELECT T1.Name ,  T3.Name ,  T3.Hours FROM Scientists AS T1 JOIN AssignedTo AS T2 ON T1.SSN = T2.Scientist JOIN Projects AS T3 ON T2.Project = T3.Code ORDER BY T3.Name ,  T1.Name

prompt: Find the day in which the difference between the max temperature and min temperature was the smallest. Also report the difference.
completion: SELECT date ,  max_temperature_f - min_temperature_f FROM weather ORDER BY max_temperature_f - min_temperature_f LIMIT 1

prompt: From which hometowns did no gymnasts come from?
completion: SELECT DISTINCT Hometown FROM people EXCEPT SELECT DISTINCT T2.Hometown FROM gymnast AS T1 JOIN people AS T2 ON T1.Gymnast_ID  =  T2.People_ID

prompt: How many states have a college with more students than average?
completion: SELECT count(DISTINCT state) FROM college WHERE enr  >  (SELECT avg(enr) FROM college)

prompt: What are the greatest and average capacity for rooms in each building?
completion: SELECT max(capacity) ,  avg(capacity) ,  building FROM classroom GROUP BY building

prompt: Find the name of the makers that produced some cars in the year of 1970?
completion: SELECT DISTINCT T1.Maker FROM CAR_MAKERS AS T1 JOIN MODEL_LIST AS T2 ON T1.Id  =  T2.Maker JOIN CAR_NAMES AS T3 ON T2.model  =  T3.model JOIN CARS_DATA AS T4 ON T3.MakeId  =  T4.id WHERE T4.year  =  '1970';

prompt: Show the name of track with most number of races.
completion: SELECT T2.name FROM race AS T1 JOIN track AS T2 ON T1.track_id  =  T2.track_id GROUP BY T1.track_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

prompt: What are the ids of the faculty members who do not advise any student.
completion: SELECT FacID FROM Faculty EXCEPT SELECT advisor FROM Student

prompt: What are the names of customers using the most popular payment method?
completion: SELECT customer_name FROM customers WHERE payment_method  =  (SELECT payment_method FROM customers GROUP BY payment_method ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1)

prompt: Find the titles of all movies not reviewed by Chris Jackson.
completion: SELECT DISTINCT title FROM Movie EXCEPT SELECT T2.title FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID JOIN Reviewer AS T3 ON T1.rID  =  T3.rID WHERE T3.name  =  'Chris Jackson'

prompt: Find the number of routes that have destination John F Kennedy International Airport.
completion: SELECT count(*) FROM airports AS T1 JOIN routes AS T2 ON T1.apid  =  T2.dst_apid WHERE T1.name  =  'John F Kennedy International Airport'

prompt: What is the average rating stars and title for the oldest movie?
completion: SELECT avg(T1.stars) ,  T2.title FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID WHERE T2.year  =  (SELECT min(YEAR) FROM Movie)

prompt: Find the number of songs in all the studio albums.
completion: SELECT count(DISTINCT T3.title) FROM albums AS T1 JOIN tracklists AS T2 ON T1.aid  =  T2.albumid JOIN songs AS T3 ON T2.songid  =  T3.songid WHERE t1.type  =  "Studio"

prompt: What are the names of the artists who sang the shortest song?
completion: SELECT T1.artist_name FROM song AS T1 JOIN files AS T2 ON T1.f_id  =  T2.f_id ORDER BY T2.duration LIMIT 1

prompt: Find the file format that is used by the most files.
completion: SELECT formats FROM files GROUP BY formats ORDER BY COUNT (*) DESC LIMIT 1

prompt: What is Nancy Edwards's address?
completion: SELECT address FROM employees WHERE first_name = "Nancy" AND last_name = "Edwards";

prompt: List the name of the shop with the latest open year.
completion: SELECT Shop_Name FROM shop ORDER BY Open_Year DESC LIMIT 1

prompt: what is the address of history department?
completion: SELECT dept_address FROM department WHERE dept_name  =  'History'

prompt: how many countries are in Asia?
completion: SELECT count(*) FROM country WHERE continent  =  "Asia"

prompt: Find the highest rank of all reviews.
completion: SELECT min(rank) FROM review

prompt: Count the number of distinct instructors who have taught a course.
completion: SELECT COUNT (DISTINCT id) FROM teaches

prompt: Show names and phones of customers who do not have address information.
completion: SELECT customer_name ,  customer_phone FROM customers WHERE customer_id NOT IN (SELECT customer_id FROM customer_address_history)

prompt: What are the manager's first name, last name and id who won the most manager award?
completion: SELECT T1.name_first ,  T1.name_last ,  T2.player_id FROM player AS T1 JOIN manager_award AS T2 ON T1.player_id  =  T2.player_id GROUP BY T2.player_id ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1;

prompt: For each submission, find its author and acceptance result.
completion: SELECT T2.Author ,  T1.Result FROM acceptance AS T1 JOIN submission AS T2 ON T1.Submission_ID  =  T2.Submission_ID

prompt: Show all cities along with the number of drama workshop groups in each city.
completion: SELECT T1.City_Town ,  count(*) FROM Addresses AS T1 JOIN Drama_Workshop_Groups AS T2 ON T1.Address_ID  =  T2.Address_ID GROUP BY T1.City_Town

prompt: Find the common personal name of course authors and students.
completion: SELECT personal_name FROM Course_Authors_and_Tutors INTERSECT SELECT personal_name FROM Students

prompt: What are the names and descriptions of the photos taken at the tourist attraction "film festival"?
completion: SELECT T1.Name ,  T1.Description FROM PHOTOS AS T1 JOIN TOURIST_ATTRACTIONS AS T2 ON T1.Tourist_Attraction_ID  =  T2.Tourist_Attraction_ID WHERE T2.Name  =  "film festival"

prompt: What are the names of any scientists who worked on projects named 'Matter of Time' and 'A Puzzling Pattern'?
completion: SELECT T3.name FROM assignedto AS T1 JOIN projects AS T2 ON T1.project  =  T2.code JOIN scientists AS T3 ON T1.scientist  =  T3.SSN WHERE T2.name  =  'Matter of Time' INTERSECT SELECT T3.name FROM assignedto AS T1 JOIN projects AS T2 ON T1.project  =  T2.code JOIN scientists AS T3 ON T1.scientist  =  T3.SSN WHERE T2.name  =  'A Puzzling Parallax'

prompt: Find the distinct last names of all the students who have president votes and whose advisor is not 2192.
completion: SELECT DISTINCT T1.LName FROM STUDENT AS T1 JOIN VOTING_RECORD AS T2 ON T1.StuID  =  PRESIDENT_Vote EXCEPT SELECT DISTINCT LName FROM STUDENT WHERE Advisor  =  "2192"

prompt: Find the building that has the largest number of faculty members.
completion: SELECT building FROM Faculty GROUP BY building ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

prompt: How many artworks are there?
completion: SELECT count(*) FROM artwork

prompt: How many pets are owned by students that have an age greater than 20?
completion: SELECT count(*) FROM student AS T1 JOIN has_pet AS T2 ON T1.stuid  =  T2.stuid WHERE T1.age  >  20

prompt: What are the minimum and maximum crime rate of counties?
completion: SELECT min(Crime_rate) ,  max(Crime_rate) FROM county_public_safety

prompt: show the titles, and authors or editors for all books made after the year 1989.
completion: SELECT book_title ,  author_or_editor FROM book_club WHERE YEAR  >  1989

prompt: display job Title, the difference between minimum and maximum salaries for those jobs which max salary within the range 12000 to 18000.
completion: SELECT job_title ,  max_salary - min_salary FROM jobs WHERE max_salary BETWEEN 12000 AND 18000

prompt: What are the names of all pilots listed by descending age?
completion: SELECT Name FROM pilot ORDER BY Age DESC

prompt: What is the name and city of the airport from most of the routes start?
completion: SELECT T1.name ,  T1.city ,  T2.src_apid FROM airports AS T1 JOIN routes AS T2 ON T1.apid  =  T2.src_apid GROUP BY T2.src_apid ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

prompt: List the names of hosts who did not serve as a host of any party in our record.
completion: SELECT Name FROM HOST WHERE Host_ID NOT IN (SELECT Host_ID FROM party_host)

prompt: List all song names by singers above the average age.
completion: SELECT song_name FROM singer WHERE age  >  (SELECT avg(age) FROM singer)

prompt: What are the companies and investors that correspond to each entrepreneur?
completion: SELECT Company ,  Investor FROM entrepreneur

prompt: List the distinct director of all films.
completion: SELECT DISTINCT Director FROM film

prompt: What are the names of movies that get 3 star and 4 star?
completion: SELECT T2.title FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID WHERE T1.stars  =  3 INTERSECT SELECT T2.title FROM Rating AS T1 JOIN Movie AS T2 ON T1.mID  =  T2.mID WHERE T1.stars  =  4

prompt: What is the city with the smallest GDP? Return the city and its GDP.
completion: SELECT city ,  GDP FROM city ORDER BY GDP LIMIT 1

prompt: What are full names and salaries of employees working in the city of London?
completion: SELECT first_name ,  last_name ,  salary FROM employees AS T1 JOIN departments AS T2 ON T1.department_id  =  T2.department_id JOIN  locations AS T3 ON T2.location_id  =  T3.location_id WHERE  T3.city  =  'London'

prompt: What is the name of the country with the most number of home airlines?
completion: SELECT country FROM airlines GROUP BY country ORDER BY count(*) DESC LIMIT 1

prompt: How many cities are there that have more than 3 airports?
completion: SELECT count(*) FROM (SELECT city FROM airports GROUP BY city HAVING count(*)  >  3)

prompt: Count the number of courses in the Physics department.
completion: SELECT count(DISTINCT course_id) FROM course WHERE dept_name  =  'Physics'
